	While We're Here
	Like an if statement, the code inside a while loop will 
	only run if the condition is true. However, a while loop 
	will continue running the code over and over until the 
	condition evaluates to false. 
	
	Incrementing While Loops
	When looping through code, it’s common to use a counter variable. 
	A counter (also known as an iterator) is a variable used in the 
	conditional logic of the loop and (usually) incremented in value 
	during each iteration through the code.
	



